words and hand gestures to convey meaning. make sure you can trust your driver before you leave your goods with him. if he shows any suspicious motives or behavior make sure you keep your bags with you. conversely, if your driver is very friendly and helpful, it is a nice gesture to buy him a little something to eat or drink when stopping for food. they will really appreciate this. your driver may in some cases act as a tout, offering to take you to businesses from which he gets baksheesh (a sort of commission). this isn't necessarily a bad 